- no obligation leaks
- losers drained
- quiescence on close
- all finalizers ran
- no ambient authority
- determinism (where applicable)

### 1) Basic lifecycle
- spawn task → complete

### 2) Nested region quiescence
- inner region closes before outer continues

### 3) Cancellation protocol end-to-end
- request cancel → checkpoint acknowledge → drain → finalize → terminal

### 4) Race with loser draining
- loser holds a resource; ensure drain releases it

### 5) Two-phase channels
- reserve/commit send; cancel mid-reserve; ensure no leaks

### 6) Obligation abort on cancellation
- hold permit then cancel; permit aborts (no leak)

### 7) Budget exhaustion behavior
- intentionally non-terminating task; verify budget-driven cancellation/termination semantics (must match the “budget exhaustion” decision bead)

### 8) Finalizer LIFO + masking
- multiple finalizers run in reverse order, even under cancellation

### 9) Deterministic replay
- same seed/config yields identical trace

### 10) Stress (many tasks)
- spawn many tasks; ensure completion and no leaks

## Acceptance Criteria
- Suite runs deterministically under lab runtime.
- Failures include:
  - formatted trace
  - invariant violation evidence
  - determinism divergence report when applicable

